.TH "cap_capset" 9 "cap_capset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cap_capset \- Validate and apply proposed changes to current's capabilities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cap_capset
.BI "(struct cred *new "  ","
.BI "const struct cred *old "  ","
.BI "const kernel_cap_t *effective "  ","
.BI "const kernel_cap_t *inheritable "  ","
.BI "const kernel_cap_t *permitted "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "new" 12
The proposed new credentials; alterations should be made here
.IP "old" 12
The current task's current credentials
.IP "effective" 12
A pointer to the proposed new effective capabilities set
.IP "inheritable" 12
A pointer to the proposed new inheritable capabilities set
.IP "permitted" 12
A pointer to the proposed new permitted capabilities set
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function validates and applies a proposed mass change to the current
process's capability sets.  The changes are made to the proposed new
credentials, and assuming no error, will be committed by the caller of LSM.
